methods.getByte:
Get a single byte from this region.

:param elementIndex: (long) - Element row key in the table's address space
:return: (byte) The byte value at the specified element row key
methods.getBytes:
Get a range of bytes from this region. Implementations are not required to verify that the range specified is
 meaningful.

:param firstElementIndex: (long) - First element row keyt in the table's address space
:param destination: (byte[]) - Array to store results
:param destinationOffset: (int) - Offset into destination to begin storing at
:param length: (int) - Number of bytes to get
:return: (byte[]) destination, to enable method chaining

text:
ColumnRegionByte implementation for regions that support fetching primitive bytes from
 column chunk page stores.
